---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/cltd.png';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About C0rvus Learns To Drink"
	pubDate={new Date('May 25 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm Samuel — based in Los Angeles, currently working as a Merchant Operations & Data Analyst at Cainiao Smart Logistics Network. My background spans logistics operations, data analysis, and front-end development.
	</p>

	<p>
		Day to day, I work with fulfillment KPIs, last-mile delivery performance, and operational workflows — the kind of work where the gap between "having data" and "making good decisions" is very real. That's what got me interested in using AI systematically, not as a novelty, but as a tool that actually changes how you work.
	</p>

	<p>
		This site documents that process — building workflows, sharpening prompts, and figuring out where AI genuinely adds leverage in real operational contexts.
	</p>

	<p>
		The name comes from the Chinese fable of the crow and the water jug — solving problems one stone at a time, through observation and iteration rather than brute force.
	</p>

	<p>
		If you're someone figuring out how to make AI genuinely useful in your work — not just in theory — this is for you.
	</p>
</Layout>